# 🛡️ HTTP in Detail – TryHackMe Notes

**📅 Date Completed:** June 23, 2025  
**🔗 TryHackMe Profile:** https://tryhackme.com/p/Tbach  
**💼 Path/Module:** Pre-security

---

## 📚 Room Summary
  This room teaches the user what HTTP and HTTPS is and how they work. It explains what happens when you put in a URL and make a request to visit a website.
Explains the four common HTTP methods and the most common HTTP status codes. For the pratical part of this room the user has to go to a external website and
make different HTTP request

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned
- HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol) is set of rules for communication with web servers for the transmitting of website data
- HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) is the secure version of HTTP
- URL (Uniform Resource Locker) is a way to access a resource on the internet
- Four common HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- What each common HTTP status code number is and what they mean
---

## 🛠️ Tools / Commands Used
- HTTP and HTTPS
- Common HTTP status code (200, 201, 301, 302, 400, 401, 403, 404, 405, 500, 503)
- Made HTTP request

